recordings.loc: Palo Verde, Imperial County, California
recordings.file-name: XC277243-ATFL _Pretty Bob_ Call Eucalyptus_Pretty Water S5645 051615 MP3.mp3
recordings.rmk: Sound amplified.  Habitat a sparse mix of mostly tamarisk and arrowweed with some mesquite and other desert vegetation.  The birds were in short vegetation (less than 2 meters off the ground) within a few meters of me.  This is an interaction between two ATFLs at a territory boundary.  They behaved aggressively towards each other, getting in to some fluttering squabbles.  Both birds were giving this call, but this recording is primarily of one individual.  The vocalizing bird is believed to be a female, as the male was detected nearby giving the territorial "Ka-breer!" call.  She had been carrying food all morning in to a mesquite about 50 meters west from where she is calling.  The nest was in this mesquite and now has at least 4 dependent young.  The agitated manner of the call and the aggressive behavior is the result of a member of a neighboring pair (believed to be the female as well) coming to the territory boundary within 50 meters of her young.  The second pair was observed multiple times carrying food in to a tamarisk about 75 meters SE of the spot this interaction took place.
